                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_færzew" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>færzew</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>угощенье</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>refreshments</q></tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>færzewmæ cæwagæ</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>любитель угощенья</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>food lover</q></tr></sense><note>(<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 121</biblScope></bibl>)</note></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Может быть, сложение из %ifær%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>para-</w></mentioned>) и %izew%i. См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zīw"/> | %izew%i ‘общественная помощь на полевых и иных работах за угощение’. В этом случае %ifær-zew%i могло означать: „то, что следует за (%ipara-%i) %izew%i“, т. е. ‘угощение’. Ср. %bскифское%b собственное имя <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Φαρζηος</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">164 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">164 ff.</biblScope></bibl></etym><etym xml:lang="en">Maybe, a compound word made of %ifær%i (← <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>para-</w></mentioned>) and %izew%i. See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_zīw"/> | %izew%i ‘public assistance in the field and other works for food’. In this case %ifær-zew%i might have meant: ‘the thing that follows (%ipara-%i) %izew%i“, i.e. ‘food’. Cf. a %bScythian%b proper name <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/> <w>Φαρζηος</w></mentioned>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">164 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">164 ff.</biblScope></bibl></etym></entry></body></text></TEI>